Dante's charming fiction has it that Juvenal (for the reason
behind the choice of him as praiser of Statius see the note to ^Purg.~
XXI.88), arriving in Limbo ca. A.D. 140, told Virgil of Statius's great
affection, which then caused a similar affection in Virgil for the
unknown Statius.  Benvenuto (comm. to these verses) offers a
sweet-tempered gloss to this passage: 'Often we love a virtuous man,
even if we have never met him -- and in just this way do I love dead
Dante.'
