Virgil wraps his delicate yet intrusive question in pledges
of friendship, and then asks Statius how such as he could have been
stained by the sin of avarice.  The phrase 'tra cotanto senno' (amidst
such wisdom) recalls the identical words found at ^Inferno~ IV.102, and
thus reminds us of the five classical poets encountered there by Dante.
<<<FORMATTING-OFF>>>
 It may also remind us that Limbo is precisely where anybody else would
<<<FORMATTING-ON>>>
have assumed Statius would spend eternity.
