at Virgil's mistake just as Dante had smiled, earlier [^Purg~.
XXI.109], at Statius's mistake.'  Statius is also obviously allowed to
be pleased to have been guilty of prodigality rather than avarice, no
matter how seriously Dante took the latter sin.
