..REFS:
EN-A20-O22-L94 A20-O22-L94
EN-A20-O22-L95 A20-O22-L95
..TEXT:
Statius's remark inevitably reminds Virgil that, even though
he is surely the greater poet, he has lost the most important contest
in life.  Diana Modesto ("Virgil, Man or shade: The 'Mancato abbraccio'
of ^Purgatorio~ XXI, 132," ^Spunti e ricerche~ 11 [1995]), p.11,
compares his role to that of Brunetto in ^Inferno~ XV.123-124, who
seems to be a winner but who has, in fact, lost everything.
