..TEXT:
Mary is presented as wanting to be sure others are fed
properly at the marriage feast in Cana of Galilee (the same biblical
scene [John 2:1-7] that furnished, in ^Purg~. XIII.29, her charitable
answer to Envy); she was not herself interested in eating, and her
mouth is rather presented as being preserved for her later task, as
intercessor, of intervening for sinners with her prayers.
